The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 02 January is 151,304 (17,438.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 28 December, there were 10,474 new confirmed cases (1,207.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 21 December, there were 8,077 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 30% (2,397 extra cases).
